[1mNAME[0m[m
       groupadd - create a new group[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
[m
       [1mgroupadd [22m[[4mOPTIONS[24m] [4mNEWGROUP[0m[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       The [1mgroupadd [22mcommand creates a new group account using the values specified on the command line plus the default values from the[m
       system. The new group will be entered into the system files as needed.[m
[m
       Groupnames may contain only lower and upper case letters, digits, underscores, or dashes. They can end with a dollar sign. Dashes[m
       are not allowed at the beginning of the groupname. Fully numeric groupnames and groupnames . or .. are also disallowed.[m
[m
       On Debian, the only constraints are that groupnames must neither start with a dash ('-') nor plus ('+') nor tilde ('~') nor[m
       contain a colon (':'), a comma (','), or a whitespace (space:' ', end of line: '\n', tabulation: '\t', etc.).[m
[m
       On Ubuntu, the same constraints as Debian are in place, with the additional constraint that the groupname cannot be fully numeric.[m
       This includes octal and hexadecimal syntax.[m
[m
       Groupnames may only be up to 32 characters long.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
       The options which apply to the [1mgroupadd [22mcommand are:[m
[m
       [1m-f[22m, [1m--force[0m[m
           This option causes the command to simply exit with success status if the specified group already exists. When used with [1m-g[22m,[m
           and the specified GID already exists, another (unique) GID is chosen (i.e.  [1m-g [22mis turned off).[m
[m
       [1m-g[22m, [1m--gid [4m[22mGID[0m[m
           The numerical value of the group's ID.  [4mGID[24m must be unique, unless the [1m-o [22moption is used. The value must be non-negative. The[m
           default is to use the smallest ID value greater than or equal to [1mGID_MIN [22mand greater than every other group.[m
[m
           See also the [1m-r [22moption and the [1mGID_MAX [22mdescription.[m
[m
       [1m-h[22m, [1m--help[0m[m
           Display help message and exit.[m
[m
       [1m-K[22m, [1m--key [4m[22mKEY[24m=[4mVALUE[0m[m
           Overrides /etc/login.defs defaults (GID_MIN, GID_MAX and others). Multiple [1m-K [22moptions can be specified.[m
[m
           Example: [1m-K [4m[22mGID_MIN[24m=[4m100[24m  [1m-K [4m[22mGID_MAX[24m=[4m499[0m[m
[m
           Note: [1m-K [4m[22mGID_MIN[24m=[4m10[24m,[4mGID_MAX[24m=[4m499[24m doesn't work yet.[m
[m
       [1m-o[22m, [1m--non-unique[0m[m
           permits the creation of a group with an already used numerical ID. As a result, for this [4mGID[24m, the mapping towards group[m
           [4mNEWGROUP[24m may not be unique.[m
[m
       [1m-p[22m, [1m--password [4m[22mPASSWORD[0m[m
           defines an initial password for the group account. PASSWORD is expected to be encrypted, as returned by [1mcrypt [22m(3).[m
