[1mNAME[0m[m
       usermod - modify a user account[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
[m
       [1musermod [22m[[4moptions[24m] [4mLOGIN[0m[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       The [1musermod [22mcommand modifies the system account files.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
       The options which apply to the [1musermod [22mcommand are:[m
[m
       [1m-a[22m, [1m--append[0m[m
           Add the user to the supplementary group(s). Use only with the [1m-G [22moption.[m
[m
       [1m-b[22m, [1m--badname[0m[m
           Allow names that do not conform to standards.[m
[m
       [1m-c[22m, [1m--comment [4m[22mCOMMENT[0m[m
           update the comment field of the user in /etc/passwd, which is normally modified using the [1mchfn[22m(1) utility.[m
[m
       [1m-d[22m, [1m--home [4m[22mHOME_DIR[0m[m
           The user's new login directory.[m
[m
           If the [1m-m [22moption is given, the contents of the current home directory will be moved to the new home directory, which is[m
           created if it does not already exist. If the current home directory does not exist the new home directory will not be created.[m
[m
       [1m-e[22m, [1m--expiredate [4m[22mEXPIRE_DATE[0m[m
           The date on which the user account will be disabled. The date is specified in the format [4mYYYY-MM-DD[24m. Integers as input are[m
           interpreted as days after 1970-01-01.[m
[m
           An input of -1 or an empty string will blank the account expiration field in the shadow password file. The account will remain[m
           available with no date limit.[m
[m
           This option requires a /etc/shadow file. A /etc/shadow entry will be created if there were none.[m
[m
       [1m-f[22m, [1m--inactive [4m[22mINACTIVE[0m[m
           defines the number of days after the password exceeded its maximum age during which the user may still login by immediately[m
           replacing the password. This grace period before the account becomes inactive is stored in the shadow password file. An input[m
           of 0 will disable an expired password with no delay. An input of -1 will blank the respective field in the shadow password[m
           file. See [1mshadow[22m(5) for more information.[m
[m
           This option requires a /etc/shadow file. A /etc/shadow entry will be created if there were none.[m
[m
       [1m-g[22m, [1m--gid [4m[22mGROUP[0m[m
           The name or numerical ID of the user's new primary group. The group must exist.[m
[m
           Any file from the user's home directory owned by the previous primary group of the user will be owned by this new group.[m
[m
           The group ownership of files outside of the user's home directory must be fixed manually.[m
