[1mNAME[0m[m
       chage - change user password expiry information[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
[m
       [1mchage [22m[[4moptions[24m] [4mLOGIN[0m[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       The [1mchage [22mcommand changes the number of days between password changes and the date of the last password change. This information[m
       is used by the system to determine when a user must change their password.[m
[m
[1mOPTIONS[0m[m
       The options which apply to the [1mchage [22mcommand are:[m
[m
       [1m-d[22m, [1m--lastday [4m[22mLAST_DAY[0m[m
           Set the number of days since January 1st, 1970 when the password was last changed. The date may also be expressed in the[m
           format YYYY-MM-DD (or the format more commonly used in your area). If the [4mLAST_DAY[24m is set to [4m0[24m the user is forced to change[m
           his password on the next log on.[m
[m
       [1m-E[22m, [1m--expiredate [4m[22mEXPIRE_DATE[0m[m
           Set the date or number of days since January 1, 1970 on which the user's account will no longer be accessible. The date may[m
           also be expressed in the format YYYY-MM-DD (or the format more commonly used in your area). A user whose account is locked[m
           must contact the system administrator before being able to use the system again.[m
[m
           For example the following can be used to set an account to expire in 180 days:[m
[m
                        chage -E $(date -d +180days +%Y-%m-%d)[m
[m
           Passing the number [4m-1[24m as the [4mEXPIRE_DATE[24m will remove an account expiration date.[m
[m
       [1m-h[22m, [1m--help[0m[m
           Display help message and exit.[m
[m
       [1m-i[22m, [1m--iso8601[0m[m
           When printing dates, use YYYY-MM-DD format.[m
[m
       [1m-I[22m, [1m--inactive [4m[22mINACTIVE[0m[m
           Set the number of days of inactivity after a password has expired before the account is locked. The [4mINACTIVE[24m option is the[m
           number of days of inactivity. A user whose account is locked must contact the system administrator before being able to use[m
           the system again.[m
[m
           Passing the number [4m-1[24m as the [4mINACTIVE[24m will remove an account's inactivity.[m
[m
       [1m-l[22m, [1m--list[0m[m
           Show account aging information.[m
[m
       [1m-m[22m, [1m--mindays [4m[22mMIN_DAYS[0m[m
           Set the minimum number of days between password changes to [4mMIN_DAYS[24m. A value of zero for this field indicates that the user[m
           may change their password at any time.[m
[m
       [1m-M[22m, [1m--maxdays [4m[22mMAX_DAYS[0m[m
