[1mNAME[0m[m
       rsync - a fast, versatile, remote (and local) file-copying tool[m
[m
[1mSYNOPSIS[0m[m
       Local:[m
           rsync [OPTION...] SRC... [DEST][m
[m
       Access via remote shell:[m
           Pull:[m
               rsync [OPTION...] [USER@]HOST:SRC... [DEST][m
           Push:[m
               rsync [OPTION...] SRC... [USER@]HOST:DEST[m
[m
       Access via rsync daemon:[m
           Pull:[m
               rsync [OPTION...] [USER@]HOST::SRC... [DEST][m
               rsync [OPTION...] rsync://[USER@]HOST[:PORT]/SRC... [DEST][m
           Push:[m
               rsync [OPTION...] SRC... [USER@]HOST::DEST[m
               rsync [OPTION...] SRC... rsync://[USER@]HOST[:PORT]/DEST)[m
[m
       Usages with just one SRC arg and no DEST arg will list the source files instead of copying.[m
[m
       The   online   version   of   this   manpage   (that   includes   cross-linking   of   topics)   is   available  at  https://down‐[m
       load.samba.org/pub/rsync/rsync.1.[m
[m
[1mDESCRIPTION[0m[m
       Rsync is a fast and extraordinarily versatile file copying tool.  It can copy locally, to/from another host over any remote shell,[m
       or to/from a remote rsync daemon.  It offers a large number of options that control every aspect of its behavior and  permit  very[m
       flexible  specification of the set of files to be copied.  It is famous for its delta-transfer algorithm, which reduces the amount[m
       of data sent over the network by sending only the differences between the source files and the existing files in the  destination.[m
       Rsync is widely used for backups and mirroring and as an improved copy command for everyday use.[m
[m
       Rsync  finds files that need to be transferred using a "quick check" algorithm (by default) that looks for files that have changed[m
       in size or in last-modified time.  Any changes in the other preserved attributes (as requested by options) are made on the  desti‐[m
       nation file directly when the quick check indicates that the file's data does not need to be updated.[m
[m
       Some of the additional features of rsync are:[m
[m
       o      support for copying links, devices, owners, groups, and permissions[m
[m
       o      exclude and exclude-from options similar to GNU tar[m
[m
       o      a CVS exclude mode for ignoring the same files that CVS would ignore[m
[m
       o      can use any transparent remote shell, including ssh or rsh[m
[m
       o      does not require super-user privileges[m
[m
       o      pipelining of file transfers to minimize latency costs[m
[m
